reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The good:The leaves look real enough. I say that because my grandmother (a gardener) thought they might be real, when she saw them (there were desks in front of the bottom half, so there could have been pots under the vines). The veins are visible on both sides, and they're decent quality, and most were not wrinkled, so if you're just sitting in a room next to them, and they're arranged like a real plant, they can easily pass for a real plant. If you examine it closely, or just drape one vine on a wall, however, it will be identified as fake.The not so good:There was (very little) shedding, initially, and none at all since arranging them the first time.As expected, I did have to hang the vines outside for a day or two, to get rid of the smell.Though the description makes it sound like there are a lot of vines in this offer, it didn't actually cover a lot of space. (see the pic). The area covered is about 3 feet wide, and 5 feet long, but as you can see, it is sparse.Overall I do recommend these, and have already purchased a second set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Decently convincing, good colour pop
reviews.reviewText: Hung these up around my room to add a bit of a green colour pop to my white walls, and make it less hospital and more hobbit cozy. these were hung up in tandem with a string light, and my printed photography stuff over my desk. They look lovely together.make sure to air them out , they have a sickly sweet smell to them at first, and give them a rather vigorous shaking as well, there’s a TON of manufacturing plastic pieces that will fall off of them like a Christmas tree.they come in long separate strands of like 8 feet each, which totally makes it easier to detangle and work with, i’ve used about half of the vines so far, but plan to add more as I work my way around my room.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars They are very nice but the smell out of the box is absolutely horrible.
reviews.reviewText: I placed them in a closed paper grocery bag to sit outside for a few weeks but that didn’t help much if at all. So I decided to donate them and put them away until I could do so.Several months later when I found them again and out of curiosity I checked the smell and by that time there was none.So I figured I might as well go ahead and use them for decorating my room divider and they look very nice….only took 6 months to get to use them!🤣

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good value, good look, but...weird smell
reviews.reviewText: I'd give this product a better review if it wasn't for the funny smell and the crazy amount of shedding and dust that came with the product. Overall, it looks very nice. It's a lovely color, and I feel like you get your bang for your buck. There is a good amount of it for the cost. When you open the package though, you get hit with this pretty obnoxious chemical smell though. It isn't overpowering or anything, but it's kind of unpleasant. They also shed these tiny little micro fibers and mine had a lot of dust inside too. I had to take them outside and give them a little shake. It still didn't stop me from sneezing all over the place though, lol. Worth the buy, for sure. But, if you're going to get them, I strongly suggest opening it up outside and maybe letting the fresh air get some of that funny smell out. I sprayed mine with some peppermint oil and that helped.

reviews.reviewText: Love the quality and the quantity of this product. They are long and can make a room feel lively. They are easy to hang and stay well

My daughter has these in her bedroom and they are nice. waterproof and bendy. there is a nasty smell to them when first opened and takes about 2 weeks to go away. 😒 overall, these are good quality and a fun decoration for your home. 😊

Ich habe dieses Produkt 2x gekauft, weil mich das Foto zu diesem Angebot sowie die positive deutsche Kundenrezension überzeugten und bin von beiden Verpackungsinhalten mega enttäuscht.Beim Öffnen der Verpackungen kam mir beide Male sehr übler Geruch und eine große Wolke Plastikstaub und entgegen, dessen Einatmen ich leider nicht ganz verhindern konnte.Nun brennen meine Schleimhäute und ich werde den Geruch nach angeschmortem Plastik seit Stunden nicht mehr aus der Nase los. Igitt! Gesund ist das garantiert nicht!Nach näherem Betrachten der Efeustränge kann ich nun sagen, die Qualität dieses künstlichen Efeus ist miserabel. Die Plastik-Stränge sind unsauber geformt und haben überall "noppelige Plastik-Nasen", die Blätter sind völlig platt, sehr dünn bis durchsichtig und zum Teil schief bedruckt.Echtem Efeu kommt dieses optisch nicht mal annähernd nahe. Das gelieferte Produkt hat mit dem im Angebot abgebildeten nicht viel gemeinsam.Ich rate von dem Kauf dieses Produktes daher ganz klar ab und werde es selbst definitiv retournieren.Leider kann ich den Verkäufer einer früheren Efeugirlanden-Bestellung von vor etwa einem Jahr bei amazon nicht mehr finden. Dieser hatte qualitativ wirklich hochwertige, ziemlich echt aussehende Kunstpflanzen zu einem ähnlichen Kaufpreis.
